✅ Your Current Setup

Right now, on your PC:
You installed SNMP → this runs the Agent (snmpd).
You also run snmpget or snmpwalk → this acts as the Manager.
So yes: both Agent and Manager are running on your PC.
Agent: listens for requests on port 161, provides system info.
Manager: sends requests to the Agent (in this case, to 127.0.0.1 = localhost).


1️⃣ What You Need

To monitor other devices (like boards, routers, or PCs) over the network, you need two things:
Agent on the target device
Each device you want to monitor must run an SNMP agent (snmpd) or support SNMP.
Many routers, switches, Linux/embedded boards already have an SNMP agent built-in or you can install it.
Manager on your PC
You already have this — snmpget or snmpwalk acts as the manager.
The manager sends requests over the network to the agent’s IP.










